03/03/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Bulgarian Deputy Prime Minister Plamen Panayotov said Tuesday (2 March) that his country is most likely to become a full-fledged member of NATO on 28 or 29 March, when it deposits its accession documents with the US government. His statement followed NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer's announcement that the six acceding states have received a formal invitation to join the Alliance.
Meanwhile, US President George W. Bush has sent a note of congratulations to his Bulgarian counterpart, Georgi Parvanov, on the national holiday Tuesday. Congratulatory telegrams have been received from leaders around the world. (Dnevnik, BTA, bTV - 03/03/04; NATO Web site, BTA, bTV - 02/03/04)
